  "text": "The workflow of PhModel generation for Chk2 inhibitors was shown in Figure 3 . In this study, we used the HypoGen program [CITATION_1] in Accelrys Discovery Studio 2.1 to generate PhModels. At the initial step, 3D conformations of the training set inhibitors were generated by using \"3D-QSAR Pharmacophore Generation protocol\" with the Best, Fast, and Caesar generating algorithms, respectively, based on the CHARMm-like force field. The conformational-space energy was constrained ≤20 kcal/mol which represented the maximum allowed energy above the global minimum energy. For each training set inhibitor, the number of the diverse 3D conformations was set to ≤255. All other parameters were set as default values. Following the above rules, the 3D conformations were generated, and then we can construct the PhModel by using \"Ligand Pharmacophore Mapping protocol. \" Each of the ten PhModels using HypoGen Best, Fast, and Caesar algorithms were generated in this study.",
